				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV>Reader's Digest version: Splitpaw = Worst pathing, EVER</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So I decided to give splitpaw a try, since it's the new hotzone, and I haven't been to 'paw since the revamp. Started pretty well, stuff is super easy, usually get 2, but so what. I pop LOD and work my way in a bit farther. I start getting strange adds, I pull two, start whacking one down, then next thing I know 1-2 more add. By the time I'm about 10 minutes from the entrance, this is happening regularly, so I start trying to figure out what the hecks happening. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So my next pull, I get one, and am sitting there meleeing away, and I get melee pushed a bit back. The elemental glares at me in frustration, turns around and runs off, doing a circuit of the room and pulling 3 others before finally pathing to me. Great, now I have 4 to contend with. This might be a bit interesting. Turns out I was right, as these 4 push me again, then turn around, run willy nilly through the depths of splitpaw and bring about 7-8 (total) elementals to the party. Death ensues, quite obviously.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have decent gear, I have decent AA's, I consider myself marginally competent, but I really don't see how this zone is usable in its current state. As it stands, if you bring&nbsp;anything less than a very solid group that is horribly overgeared for the content, or an enchanter that is really on his toes, you'll wipe to a pathing train. Which is really too bad, I was kind of enjoying mucking about and visiting a zone I haven't seen in ages, now there's no way I'll bother going back.</DIV>
				
				</td></tr>
